booleanSAT

Class BooleanSatisfiabilitySolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • framework.ConstraintSolver
      • booleanSAT.BooleanSatisfiabilitySolver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class BooleanSatisfiabilitySolver
extends ConstraintSolver
    The BooleanSatisfiabilitySolver provides a means to reason upon Boolean Satisfiability constraint problems. It is based on the off the shelf SAT4J solver, available at www.sat4j.org. The solver's variables are BooleanVariables, which can be bound by BooleanConstraints. The latter are disjunctive Boolean clauses, thus the collection of all BooleanConstraints in a ConstraintNetwork represents a well-formed-formula (wff) in Conjunctive Normal Form (CNF). Note that BooleanConstraints can be instantiated with a factory method from non-CNF formulas (see BooleanConstraint.createBooleanConstraints(BooleanVariable[], String).
    Author:
    Federico Pecora
